SIMPLE: privacy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Privacy
<hw>Pri"va*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Privacies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[See
<er>Private</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being in
retirement from the company or observation of others;
seclusion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place of seclusion from company or observation;
retreat; solitude; retirement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her sacred <qex>privacies</qex> all open lie.</q>
<rj><qau>Rowe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Concealment of what is said or done.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A private matter; a secret.</def>
<rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>See <er>Privity</er>, 2.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Privado</ent>⟦br⟧
